Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.25,0:01:36.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ladies and gentlemen,\ngood evening.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:38.02,0:01:43.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My friend invited three families to his villa,\nwhere a forbidden past lay dormant.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.96,0:01:48.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,When that soul which had been\ninterred there returned to life,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.30,0:01:54.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...I sensed clearly that a new vengeance\nwas about to sprout.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.64,0:02:06.64,count fo,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 9:\NI Dreamed A Dark Dream
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.66,0:02:19.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.30,0:02:21.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Somebody, send for\na doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.17,0:02:23.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.13,0:02:25.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's Madame Danglars!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.90,0:02:28.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's collapsed!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.31,0:02:36.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell\nare you after?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.41,0:02:38.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's your game?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.32,0:02:45.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Surely you jest. My only goal is to\Nhave my guests enjoy the party.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.59,0:02:52.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You've gone too far! This manor was\noriginally owned by my father-in-law.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.80,0:02:56.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If you're deliberately trying to insult me,\NI'll make you regret it!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.64,0:03:07.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even though I was unaware of that fact,\NI have indeed been most rude.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.38,0:03:11.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, this is a\nmost fascinating,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.08,0:03:15.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...not to mention\nmost odd, coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.69,0:03:22.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which means, then, that this place is as\nfamiliar to you as the back of your hand.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.13,0:03:29.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In which case, my little entertainment\nwas unfair from the very beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.93,0:03:35.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,This simply won't do.\NShall we start over and try it again?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.81,0:03:39.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world happened, Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.65,0:03:47.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not really sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.85,0:03:51.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As part of the game, I was about to give\NMadame Victoria the box with the prize in it,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.49,0:03:53.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and the instant I did, she...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.13,0:04:02.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What in the world\nmade her faint?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.70,0:04:06.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,H-How can this be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.04,0:04:10.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Dear boy, forgive me...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.54,0:04:14.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to be a case of anemia.\NIt is nothing serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.51,0:04:19.64,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you again.\NWho ARE you?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.45,0:04:23.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Exactly what do\nyou know?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.92,0:04:26.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Your life depends on\nyour answer.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.76,0:04:29.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.03,0:04:35.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am but a poor bumpkin who has come from\nthe far reaches of Eastern Space.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.97,0:04:40.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Other than that, I have no past\nwhich is worth speaking of.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:43.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,None at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.78,0:04:51.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Victoria!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.58,0:04:55.98,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Victoria! What's happened\nto her?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.75,0:05:00.38,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You needn't worry.\NShe is merely feeling out of sorts.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.66,0:05:02.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Honey! Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.33,0:05:07.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I expect that a few moments' rest\nwill have her feeling good as new.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.36,0:05:10.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Is that not right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.17,0:05:13.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Eugenie?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.57,0:05:14.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let's look for her!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.44,0:05:17.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:21.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eugenie!\NWhere are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.98,0:05:29.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Father! Eugenie!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.42,0:05:35.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You there!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.43,0:05:41.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know where Eugenie is?\NShe's Monsieur Danglars' daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.80,0:05:45.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard stories about you\nfrom the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.94,0:05:47.43,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,All sorts of things.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.80,0:05:51.36,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,So, you're Albert, son of\nthe Morcerf family...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.91,0:05:57.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Eugenie?\NIsn't she with you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.81,0:06:02.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She's already headed towards the inner\nchambers, both she and your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.92,0:06:05.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Let me make one thing\nperfectly clear to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.42,0:06:15.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,In all the world, I am the only person capable\nof understanding the Count's feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.77,0:06:16.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Wha...?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.03,0:06:19.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now, if you'll excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.12,0:07:07.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Count!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.78,0:07:09.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Give me your hand, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.89,0:07:13.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,My thanks, Bertuccio...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.29,0:07:16.26,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What are those markings...?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.23,0:07:21.79,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'd ask you not to overexert yourself,\nbut I'd probably be wasting my breath.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.37,0:07:26.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have it in you to follow me?\NInto the darkest depths of Hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.00,0:07:30.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course. I'll be at your side\nwherever you go, Gankutsuou.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.79,0:07:48.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Gankutsuou?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.19,0:07:50.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mother...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.93,0:07:53.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm all right.\NI'm fine now.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.93,0:07:56.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry if I worried you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.16,0:08:21.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.96,0:08:24.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.76,0:08:26.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry\nabout earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.66,0:08:29.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I got carried away without stopping\nto consider your feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.30,0:08:35.07,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm the one who should apologize.\NI said such rude things.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.84,0:08:42.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I'm glad. It's nice that you two\ncan have a normal conversation now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.95,0:08:46.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I... had misjudged him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.98,0:08:51.15,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad we had this\nchance to talk.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.65,0:08:53.12,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As am I!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.32,0:09:00.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Now that all the excitement's over,\NI feel kinda...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.34,0:09:07.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.64,0:09:13.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.28,0:09:16.80,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hold on!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.05,0:09:19.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:20.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Monsieur Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.83,0:09:34.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How are you feeling?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.36,0:09:38.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It feels like a weight on my chest\nhas been lifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.40,0:09:43.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I am glad to hear it.\NI mixed this medicine especially for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.44,0:09:47.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing is better for the\ntreatment of chest pains.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:50.31,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry if I made\nany trouble for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.65,0:09:53.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,For some reason, I felt sick\nall of a sudden...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.82,0:09:57.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What could be wrong\nwith Albert?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.29,0:10:01.95,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since we were kids,\Nhe's never had so much as a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.06,0:10:06.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You and Albert are\nchildhood friends, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.60,0:10:07.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.93,0:10:10.09,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I heard all about it from\NMademoiselle Valentine.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.53,0:10:15.87,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,She said that she has always been jealous\nof how close you two are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.24,0:10:18.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's just because we've known\neach other for so long.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.61,0:10:21.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's not just because you're\nold friends, is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.48,0:10:30.01,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I somehow get the impression that you two\nshare a bond that no one else can share in.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.75,0:10:35.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Speaking of which, how long have\nyou had feelings for Valentine?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.89,0:10:39.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That's an awkward question\nto be asked by her fiancée.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.63,0:10:42.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Of course, you're right.\NI'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.67,0:10:45.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, I am the one who\nis at fault here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.54,0:10:54.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But if you love her, that should be\nall that matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.64,0:10:57.81,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,There you go, saying such\nirresponsible things again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.48,0:11:02.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Irresponsible, huh?\NI suppose it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.79,0:11:04.05,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's a strange thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.15,0:11:09.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't you love Mademoiselle Valentine?\NShe is your fiancée, after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.16,0:11:14.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What about you? Will you stop loving her\njust because you can't marry her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.63,0:11:15.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,As to that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.10,0:11:21.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You can't, can you? You can't simply\nfall out of love, can you?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.84,0:11:26.67,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Even if it's a relationship where\nyou can't marry the person.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.08,0:11:30.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are you saying that you harbor\na hopeless love for someone, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.51,0:11:36.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Marriage isn't necessarily the only way\nto make that person happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.39,0:11:39.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you think?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.03,0:11:49.02,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I hadn't thought of that...\NPerhaps you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.64,0:11:55.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valentine's found herself\na great guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.64,0:11:58.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.51,0:11:59.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.51,0:12:04.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I realize that this is an odd question,\nbut what have you eaten today?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.08,0:12:08.85,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I've been so busy today\nthat I haven't eaten anything at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.75,0:12:15.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But now that you mention it, I drank some\nwater from the table with the blue flowers.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.93,0:12:20.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The table with blue flowers was\nthe Villefort family's table.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.33,0:12:22.76,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think that has\nanything to do with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:25.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, I would like you\nto remain calm and listen to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.07,0:12:30.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What had been attacking\nyour body... was poison.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.47,0:12:32.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Poison?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.54,0:12:38.34,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, a fearful poison that is called\N"zhen-du" in Eastern Space.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.45,0:12:40.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're saying that the\nwater was poisoned?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.68,0:12:42.62,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It would be safe\nto assume so.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.19,0:12:47.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You managed to survive because the ice\nhad melted, thus diluting the poison,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.32,0:12:50.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but you nevertheless\nhad a close call.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.89,0:12:52.83,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who would do\nsuch a thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.63,0:12:56.66,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I suspect that you were\nnot the target.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.87,0:13:01.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Right. The poison was mixed\ninto that water pitcher,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.30,0:13:04.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...so that means the target\nwas the Villefort family.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.58,0:13:07.91,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.18,0:13:11.58,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Feelings of hatred and jealousy\ntowards another...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.48,0:13:18.72,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...are emotions which silently fester and grow,\nunbeknownst to the object of their affection.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:23.18,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The happier that person is,\nthe less aware he is of their feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.59,0:13:26.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,However, their attempt\nended in failure.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.90,0:13:29.45,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Which means that they\nwill lay another trap to...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.57,0:13:33.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,They can't! There are people\nthat I want to be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.81,0:13:41.00,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert, are you sure you\nshould be out of bed?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.24,0:13:43.47,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I feel fine now.\NSorry I made you worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.78,0:13:46.54,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, I think you should\ntake it easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.75,0:13:48.65,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's right,\NMonsieur Albert.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.75,0:13:50.41,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No, we have\nto hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.89,0:13:54.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll explain later. Anyway, we have\nto get to Valentine's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.62,0:13:56.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,To Mademoiselle\NValentine's house?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.66,0:13:58.94,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.00,0:14:07.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're such a\nfrightening man...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.80,0:14:12.60,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And at the same time,\nso very alluring...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.70,0:14:36.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Are we clear on this,\NBoville?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.50,0:14:41.70,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Use every network at your disposal and find out\neverything there is to know about that man.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.84,0:14:45.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Focus your investigation\non Marseilles in particular.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.91,0:14:46.97,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Understood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.64,0:14:52.27,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,"Count of Monte Cristo," my ass. Mark my\nwords, I'll find out who you really are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.35,0:15:02.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Incidentally, what is your connection\nto this man, Your Honor?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.62,0:15:05.29,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That isn't something that you need\nto concern yourself about.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.26,0:15:11.22,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. But I suggest that\nyou be mindful of rats.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.33,0:15:14.33,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.44,0:15:15.73,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be off, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.55,0:15:30.61,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Look, Grandfather.\NIsn't this a beautiful rosary?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.56,0:15:41.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Pardon me.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.93,0:15:44.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I've brought you something\nto drink.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.93,0:15:46.90,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, Valois.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.96,0:16:11.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Still, don't you think the Count\nis reading too much into this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.53,0:16:13.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I mean, come on, someone's trying\nto kill the Villefort family?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.03,0:16:18.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He's not like other people.\NI believe him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.44,0:16:24.23,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Say, Franz...\NWill you hear me out?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.77,0:16:27.24,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's up? You sound\nawfully serious.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.98,0:16:30.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The thing is, I finally\nfigured something out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.21,0:16:32.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well? What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.02,0:16:35.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You might laugh at me for\nsaying this, Franz,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.38,0:16:39.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...but I really do think it's important for\nthe two people to love each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.02,0:16:41.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's gotten into you?\NWhat brought this on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.29,0:16:48.75,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I... It's just that I want Valentine\nand Maximilien to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.83,0:16:52.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I know it's more complicated\nthan that for you, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.90,0:16:56.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Not at all. I want the same\nthing with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.07,0:17:01.44,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,If it's humanly possible, I think two people\nwho love each other should be together.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.61,0:17:02.77,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You do, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.85,0:17:07.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The love those two have is the real thing.\NI want them to be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.58,0:17:12.11,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,No way am I gonna let\nanybody poison her!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.09,0:17:19.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,The rain has certainly\ngotten stronger...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.76,0:17:24.49,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's rather humid,\nisn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.80,0:17:27.63,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You must be hot, Valois.\NWould you like a glass, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.50,0:17:31.20,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? No, I couldn't possibly,\NMademoiselle.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.31,0:17:33.37,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right, don't stand\non ceremony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.78,0:17:43.88,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valois!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.66,0:17:49.42,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valois, what's the matter?\NValois!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.52,0:17:52.19,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,M-Mademoiselle...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.59,0:17:53.56,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valois?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.86,0:17:55.99,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Valois!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.83,0:18:00.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,W-What happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.28,0:18:11.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Grandfather...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.68,0:18:45.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.18,0:18:47.51,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry, call the doctor!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.69,0:18:52.35,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Mademoiselle Valentine!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.82,0:18:56.78,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,How can this be?\NMademoiselle Valentine!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.23,0:19:06.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe it.\NIt's just like the Count said.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.10,0:19:10.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell\nis going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.28,0:19:15.14,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.51,0:19:16.57,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.78,0:19:19.30,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Where else?\NTo go see the Count.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.65,0:19:21.84,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,He might be able to do\nsomething for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.32,0:19:24.48,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Albert!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.56,0:19:29.08,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Albert...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.69,0:19:34.69,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be at your side wherever\nyou go, Gankutsuou.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.77,0:19:44.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry, but His Excellency is away\non a business trip at the moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.34,0:19:47.74,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You're kidding!\NWhen will he be back?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.94,0:19:53.25,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,That is entirely up to His Excellency.\NI'm sorry I cannot be of more help.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.49,0:20:04.55,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I see that you're helpless by\nyourself, same as always.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.96,0:20:05.82,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.09,0:20:08.96,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking forward to seeing\nhow this turns out.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.13,0:20:11.53,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,What's that supposed\nto mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.83,0:20:15.46,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have the courage to learn\nwhat the future holds?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.27,0:20:20.40,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.29,0:20:36.59,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!\NWhat am I gonna do?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.51,0:20:57.50,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Don't die, Valentine!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:59.08,0:21:01.71,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You child of illicit love who has\nawoken from a dark dream...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.45,0:21:06.89,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,...and come back to life\nfrom the depths of death...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.79,0:21:13.39,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,You beautiful child who knows nothing\nof love, nor of being loved.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.67,0:21:17.93,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thou art anathema.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.57,0:21:22.04,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Thou art anathema!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.85,0:23:15.32,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,A dark cloud spreads out like\na stain to cover our lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.58,0:23:19.28,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,And a letter arrives from an old friend\Nwho was thought to be dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.95,0:23:22.52,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Next time on Gankutsuou,\NThe Count of Monte Cristo act 10:
Dialogue: 0,0:23:20.92,0:23:22.88,count fo,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(352,350)}Act 10:\NThe Letter From Edmond
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.52,0:23:23.86,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,..."The Letter\NFrom Edmond."
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.39,0:23:27.16,count main,Comment,0000,0000,0000,,Bide your time,\nand hold out hope!
